<h2 id="guidelines">Guidelines</h2>
<h3 id="title">Selecting tree items</h3>
<p>Other than styles applied by the presence of the <code>selected</code> attribute, selecting items is owned by the application. This usually means setting up basic click handlers:</p>
<h3 id="accessibility">Accessibility</h3>
<p>The root tree should have <code>role="tree"</code> and <code>aria-label="..."</code>. Nested trees and tree items should have <code>role="treeitem"</code>. Here's an example:</p>
<code-sample readonly>
  <m-tree role="tree" aria-label="Your family tree">
    <m-treeitem>Item 2</m-treeitem>
    <m-treeitem>Item 1</m-treeitem>
    <m-tree>
      <m-treeitem>Sub-item 1</m-treeitem>
      <m-treeitem>Sub-item 2</m-treeitem>
      <m-treeitem>Sub-item 3</m-treeitem>
    </m-tree>
    <m-treeitem>Item 3</m-treeitem>
  </m-tree>
</code-sample>

